               <p>183. <persName id="def1-183-18491126" type="defendantName">
                     <interp inst="def1-183-18491126" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-183-18491126" type="surname" value="PAYNE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-183-18491126" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">WILLIAM PAYNE</hi>
                  </persName>
                  <rs id="t18491126-183-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18491126-183-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18491126-183-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="pocketpicking"></interp>, stealing 1 handkerchief, value 3<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.; the goods of <persName id="t18491126-name-1063" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18491126-name-1063" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18491126-name-1063" type="surname" value="WYATT"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18491126-name-1063" type="given" value="JOHN WILLIAM"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18491126-183-offence-1 t18491126-name-1063"></join>John William Wyatt</persName>, from his person.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. DAWSON</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">conducted the Prosecution.</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">JOHN WILLIAM WYATT</hi>. I am a clerk in the Provincial Bank of Ireland, Old Broad-street. On 3<hi rend="italic">rd</hi> Nov. I was in the Borough, about half-past five o'clock—I had left the bank, about five minutes past five—I had my pocket-handkerchief then—in High-street, in the Borough, I felt a person take it—I turned round and saw two persons running—I could not identify them—the prisoner is about the size of one of them—they were about a middling height; a person spoke to me—I afterwards saw the prisoner at the police-court—I have not seen my handkerchief since.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. PAYNE</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">IS</hi> not this the first time you have said anything about two persons running away? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> I think not—(Me <hi rend="italic">depo-sition being referred to did, not contain it</hi>)—I must have omitted it, 1 did not think much of it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. DAWSON</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Where was Arkwright? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> He appeared to me to be looking in one of the shops—the persons were running towards London Bridge, and were about 100 yards behind me.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18491126-name-1064" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18491126-name-1064" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18491126-name-1064" type="surname" value="ARKWRIGHT"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18491126-name-1064" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES ARKWRIGHT</persName>
                  </hi>. I live in Wilderness-street, Long-lane, and am a currier. On Saturday afternoon, 3<hi rend="italic">rd</hi> Nov., I saw Wyatt in the Borough, from a quarter to half-past five—I had seen the prisoner follow two or three gentlemen before—then Wyatt and his friend came past—the prisoner followed them for about a minute—he then took the handkerchief and ran away—I ran about twenty yards after him, but found I could not overtake him—I turned and went to the prosecutor, knowing the prisoner well before. <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> How many times have you been a witness? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> I have had fourteen or fifteen convictions—if I see persons do wrong I think it is my duty to have them brought up—I do not know that it is better pay than being a currier—I do not know that there is any pay—I have got the same as others—I had 3<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. a day in the other Court. <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <rs id="t18491126-183-verdict-1" type="verdictDescription">
                        <interp inst="t18491126-183-verdict-1" type="verdictCategory" value="notGuilty"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18491126-183-verdict-1" type="verdictSubcategory" value=""></interp>NOT GUILTY</rs>
                  </hi>.</p>
